.TH "access_remote_vm" 9 "access_remote_vm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
access_remote_vm \- access another process' address space
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" access_remote_vm
.BI "(struct mm_struct *mm "  ","
.BI "unsigned long addr "  ","
.BI "void *buf "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "unsigned int gup_flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mm" 12
the mm_struct of the target address space
.IP "addr" 12
start address to access
.IP "buf" 12
source or destination buffer
.IP "len" 12
number of bytes to transfer
.IP "gup_flags" 12
flags modifying lookup behaviour
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The caller must hold a reference on \fImm\fP.
